    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 311.523/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform your
                    excellency that the Government of His Majesty the King of Spain has decided upon
                    the removal of the remains of the thirty-three Spanish sailors who died while
                    prisoners in the United States as members of the crew of Admiral Cervera’s
                    squadron and were buried in the Naval Cemetery of Seavey Island.</p>
                <p>I should be thankful to your excellency if you would ask your colleague the
                    Secretary of the Navy kindly to order that no obstacle be opposed to the
                    transfer of the remains when the time comes.</p>
                <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
